UNinstall Webstrom
go to ubuntu software and remove the webstrom
Then, go to home and press cant+h to show the .webstrom and hit this command with your webstrom version

rm -rf ~/.WebStorm9



First install java (If you don't have):

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:webupd8team/java
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install oracle-java8-installer
sudo apt-get install oracle-java8-set-default


go to this link, select linux and click on download
https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/#section=linux


go to downloads and hit the following command , with there wevstrom version

tar xfz WebStorm-2016.2.4.tar.gz 
cd WebStorm-162.1121.31/
cd bin/
chmod -R 755 webstorm.sh 
./webstorm.sh




